      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "For a bad headache, a standard dose of acetaminophen is usually 500mg to 1000mg, but you must strictly adhere to the maximum daily limit on the bottle. Do not exceed the recommended dosage, as too much acetaminophen can stress your liver, which is another important organ. If you are still unsure about the exact limit for your medical history, stick to the lowest effective dose and monitor how you feel.",
